a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Designs.ai is best suited for small businesses, marketers, non designers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Stencil, meanwhile, shines for social media managers, bloggers, quick image needs, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2019, Designs.ai describes itself as \"All-in-one AI creative platform for logos, videos, mockups, and copy.\" Stencil, established in 2015, positions itself as \"Fast and simple image creation tool optimized for social media posts.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Designs.ai** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (6.0 vs 5.0), more features (7 vs 4). However, this does not mean Stencil is a poor choice — far from it. Stencil excels in its own right, particularly for social media managers and bloggers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value multiple design tools in one platform, go with Designs.ai. If extremely fast image creation matters more to you, Stencil is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
